00:12:59.540 --> 00:13:02.029
on an ancient book while reciting its verses.

00:13:02.029 --> 00:13:06.180
Since then, Bee has been traveling from different
places to prey on young

00:13:06.180 --> 00:13:07.529
boys like him.

00:13:07.529 --> 00:13:11.290
Although she offers to let him join her cult
and tell the cops that they are innocent,

00:13:11.290 --> 00:13:14.040
Cole refuses and burns the spellbook anyway.

00:13:14.040 --> 00:13:16.779
This time Bee's charms do not work on him
anymore.

00:13:16.779 --> 00:13:20.670
He runs to Melanie's house to take her dad's
car; he drives it recklessly into his house

00:13:20.670 --> 00:13:23.199
while Bee is distracted by the burning book.

00:13:23.199 --> 00:13:25.699
The vehicle crashes directly into her.

00:13:25.699 --> 00:13:27.230
Cole climbs out of the wrecked car.

00:13:27.230 --> 00:13:31.540
They have one last emotional farewell as they
reminisce about their friendship.

00:13:31.540 --> 00:13:35.410
Bee initiates to do their handshake, but Cole
leaves her to die alone.

00:13:35.410 --> 00:13:39.949
The police officers and firefighters arrive
at the house for rescue operations.

00:13:39.949 --> 00:13:42.190
His parents come and rush to embrace him.

00:13:42.190 --> 00:13:48.160
He tells his parents that he no longer needs
a babysitter anymore.

